==English==
===Etymology===
From [[diazo]] + [[ammonium]]
===Noun===
'''diazonium'''
#{{chemistry}} any [[univalent]] [[cation]], of [[general formula]] R-N<sub>2</sub><sup>+</sup>, where R is an [[aryl]] group; diazonium [[salt]]s are used to manufacture [[azo dye]]s, and take part in the [[Sandmeyer reaction]]

